body.prompt:
Generate a fake conversation between a customer and an agent.
The agent should introduce themselves, their company and give the customer
their name. The agent should ask for the customer's name.
As part of the conversation, have the agent ask for two pieces of
personal information.  Spell out numbers. For example, 1000 should be
said as one zero zero zero, not one thousand. The conversation should be
at least 10 lines long and be complete. At the end
of the conversation, the agent should thank the customer for their time
and end the conversation. Return the conversation formatted 
like the following example:

{'conversation': 
    [
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': 'xxxxx'}, 
    {'speaker': 'Customer', 'message': "xxxxx."}, 
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': "xxxxxx"}
    ] 
}

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Hello, my name is Jordan Bailey and I'm with XYZ Car Dealership. May I have your name, please?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Hello, my name is Hannah Edwards.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Nice to meet you, Hannah. Could you kindly provide me with your phone number, digit by digit?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Sure, it's five zero five, six seven eight, two three four five.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you, Hannah. And could you please confirm the last four digits of your social security number?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Of course, they are one two three four.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Great, thanks for sharing that information, Hannah. Is there any specific concern or question you have regarding the data management at the Car Dealership?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: No, I'm feeling relieved as everything seems to be in order now.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: That's wonderful to hear, Hannah. Thank you for your time and for choosing XYZ Car Dealership. Please don't hesitate to contact us for any future assistance. Have a great day!
